<document xml:lang="en">
    <header>
        <title>Installation on iOS (iPhone / iPad / iPod)</title>
    </header>
    <body>
        <p>After downloading the app from the App Store, your homle screen could
            look like this:
        </p>

        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_keyboard_home_screen.no.png" alt="Home screen with Sami Keyboards"/>
        </p>
        <p>Open the app:</p>
        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_sami_keyboards_app.no.png" alt="The app page."/>
        </p>
        <p>Press the link «Open Preferences»</p>
        <p>Select
<strong>
«General &gt; Keyboard &gt; Keyboards &gt; Add new keyboard...»
</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_general.no.png"          alt="Select General"/>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_keyboard.no.png"         alt="Select Keyboard"/>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_keyboards.no.png"        alt="Select Keyboards"/>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_add_new_keyboard.no.png" alt="Select Add new keyboard..."/>
        </p>

        <p>Under the text «Third party keyboards» choose «Sami keyboards»:</p>

        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_select_sami_keyboards.no.png" alt="Select Sami Keyboards"/>
        </p>
        <p>Enable the keyboards you want to use:</p>
        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_enable_keyboards.no.png" alt="Enable keyboards"/>
        </p>
        <p>The installation is done!</p>

        <p>To switch to a Sami keyboards, touch and hold the globe key to the
            left of the space key:</p>
        <p>
            <img width="213" src="images/ios_select_active_keyboard.no.png" alt="Keyboard selection menu"/>
        </p>

        <p>You may also just touch the globe key repeated times till you get th
            keyboard you want.</p>

        <p>Please note that touch-and-hold does not work when one of the Sami
            keyboards is active. This is a <link
        href="https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/General/Conceptual/ExtensibilityPG/Keyboard.html"
        >limitation by Apple</link> («there is no API to obtain a list of
        enabled keyboards or for picking a particular keyboard to switch to»),
        and concerns all third party keyboards.</p>

    </body>
</document>
